Several of our users have been confused by the fact that if you view and then edit a saved filter, edit the JQL that defines the filter (in Advanced mode) or change any custom field (in Simple mode) and then click the "*Save as* new filter" link that what will be saved is not the filter defined by the changes you just specified, but instead a copy of the original saved filter.  A solution to this would be to gray out that link any time a query has been edited but the "Search" button has not yet been clicked.

